n","label":"Scenic","value":"High"},{"icon":"footprints","label":"Walking","value":"Moderate"},{"icon":"cloud-rain","label":"Rain Safety","value":"Medium"},{"icon":"users","label":"Family Fit","value":"Good"},{"icon":"scale","label":"Balance","value":"Mixed"}],"galleryItems":[{"id":1,"type":"video","src":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518509562904-e7ef99cdcc86?w=1200&q=80","location":"Route Overview","atmosphere":"The day at a glance","alt":"Southwest Jeju route overview"},{"id":2,"type":"photo","src":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506744038136-46273834b3fb?w=800&q=80","location":"Hallasan opening","atmosphere":"Cool mountain start","alt":"Hallasan Eoseungsaengak trail"},{"id":3,"type":"photo","src":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500530855697-b586d89ba3ee?w=800&q=80","location":"Basalt coast","atmosphere":"Volcanic shoreline drama","alt":"Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff coastline"},{"id":4,"type":"photo","src":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1441974231531-c6227db76b6e?w=800&q=80","location":"Waterfall forest walk","atmosphere":"Cool green contrast","alt":"Cheonjeyeon Falls forest path"},{"id":5,"type":"photo","src":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1495474472287-4d71bcdd2085?w=800&q=80","location":"Tea-field pause","atmosphere":"Open green calm","alt":"O’Sulloc Tea Museum and tea-field atmosphere"},{"id":6,"type":"video","src":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507525428034-b723cf961d3e?w=800&q=80","location":"Aewol coast finish","atmosphere":"Late-day release","alt":"Aewol coastal café street"}],"itineraryStops":[{"number":1,"time":"09:00","duration":"70 min","name":"Hallasan Eoseungsaengak","category":"Short Hallasan Trail","description":"The day begins on Hallasan while the air is cooler and the group still has fresh energy. Eoseungsaengak is one of the shortest and most approachable Hallasan routes, so it gives the tour a real mountain start without turning the day into a full hike.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506744038136-46273834b3fb?w=800&q=80","highlights":["Short Hallasan trail with a rewarding summit feel","Wide views over Jeju City, oreum landscapes, and Hallasan''s upper slopes","A stronger nature opening than a simple roadside viewpoint","Good balance between activity and accessibility for mixed-age groups"],"timeUsed":["Arrival, trail briefing, and quick pace check","Main uphill walk to the viewpoint area","Short summit stay, photos, and descent"],"whyOnRoute":"Starting here uses the group''s energy well and gives the rest of the day a clearer highland-to-coast storyline.","visitBasics":{"hours":"Trail entry from 05:00; seasonal cutoff applies","closed":"Weather-dependent restrictions possible","admission":"Free","walking":"Moderate; short but stair-heavy"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Eorimok entrance area","parking":"Available"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"Open ridge views work better than tight close-ups once the group reaches the higher viewpoint zones.","facilities":"Best facilities are at the trailhead, not on the route itself.","tip":"This stop feels shortest when treated as a focused scenic hike, not a slow wander with many pauses."}},{"number":2,"time":"10:50","duration":"40 min","name":"Daepo Jusangjeolli Cliff","category":"Basalt Coastline","description":"After the Hallasan start, the route opens dramatically at the sea. Jusangjeolli brings in one of Jeju''s most iconic volcanic coastlines, where columnar basalt cliffs meet strong ocean movement and give the day its first big coastal moment.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500530855697-b586d89ba3ee?w=800&q=80","highlights":["Jeju''s signature hexagonal basalt cliff formations","Strong sea views with powerful visual contrast after the mountain trail","Compact stop with high scenic payoff","Clear geology story that ties naturally back to Hallasan"],"timeUsed":["Arrival and short orientation at the entrance area","Main viewing walk along the coastal platform","Photo time and regroup before departure"],"whyOnRoute":"It shifts the day from mountain terrain into Jeju''s volcanic coastline without losing the geology thread.","visitBasics":{"hours":"09:00-18:00 (Last entry 17:40)","closed":"Open year-round","admission":"Adults 2,000 / Children & Youth 1,000 KRW","walking":"Easy"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Entrance area","parking":"Paid parking"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"Side-angle shots usually capture the basalt pattern and surf better than center-framed photos.","facilities":"Facilities are simple but efficient near the entrance.","tip":"Wind and sea spray can change the feel of this stop quickly, so the pace stays tighter here."}},{"number":3,"time":"11:50","duration":"60 min","name":"Lunch","category":"Midday Reset","description":"Lunch sits between the dramatic south-coast stops and the softer tea-and-café finish. It works as a true reset point, giving the group time to recover from the morning hike and enjoy the second half at a more relaxed rhythm.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1414235077428-338989a2e8c0?w=800&q=80","highlights":["Natural break after the Hallasan and cliff segment","Better pacing for mixed-age groups","Clean transition into the waterfall and tea-field sequence","Keeps the late-day Aewol stop feeling relaxed, not rushed"],"timeUsed":["Arrival and seating","Meal and short rest","Departure preparation for the next scenic stop"],"whyOnRoute":"Placing lunch here keeps the day balanced and prevents the first half from feeling too activity-heavy.","visitBasics":{"hours":"Restaurant hours","closed":"Varies","admission":"Included or à la carte","walking":"Minimal"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Restaurant facilities","parking":"Available"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"This is the best stop for food shots if the group wants a more lifestyle-style gallery.","facilities":"Full restaurant amenities.","tip":"A steady lunch break improves the entire late-day rhythm more than trying to save a few minutes."}},{"number":4,"time":"13:00","duration":"50 min","name":"Cheonjeyeon Falls","category":"Waterfall & Forest Walk","description":"Cheonjeyeon brings a cooler, greener mood after the exposed cliff stop. Bridges, forested paths, and waterfall viewpoints give the route a softer scenic layer before the day opens again toward Jeju''s tea fields and northwest coast.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1441974231531-c6227db76b6e?w=800&q=80","highlights":["Waterfall viewpoints with a more shaded and tranquil atmosphere","Bridge-and-forest walking sequence that changes the day''s texture","A scenic stop that feels cooler after the south-coast exposure","Good contrast before the tea-field and café-coast finish"],"timeUsed":["Arrival and route explanation at the entrance","Main walking segment through the waterfall grounds","Viewpoint stops, photos, and return"],"whyOnRoute":"It softens the route after Jusangjeolli and prepares the group for a calmer late-day sequence.","visitBasics":{"hours":"09:00-17:50 (Last admission 17:10)","closed":"Open year-round","admission":"Adults 2,500 / Teenagers & Children 1,350 KRW","walking":"Moderate; stairs and wet surfaces possible"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Entrance area","parking":"Available"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"Layered bridge-and-waterfall compositions work better than trying to frame every element in one shot.","facilities":"Basic facilities are concentrated near the entrance.","tip":"This stop feels best at a steady pace because stairs and slippery patches can slow the group naturally."}},{"number":5,"time":"14:20","duration":"60 min","name":"O’Sulloc Tea Museum","category":"Tea Fields & Museum Stop","description":"After the waterfall walk, O’Sulloc opens the route into a calmer tea-field mood. The museum, shop, and surrounding green tea landscape add a softer lifestyle layer to the day before the final Aewol coast finish.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1495474472287-4d71bcdd2085?w=800&q=80","highlights":["Jeju tea-field scenery with a calmer open landscape","Tea-culture stop that feels lighter after the forest walk","Strong photo value with green rows, modern architecture, and desserts","Natural transition between scenic sightseeing and the relaxed Aewol finish"],"timeUsed":["Arrival and short orientation around the museum zone","Tea-field views, museum or shop browsing, and café time","Meet-up and departure toward Aewol"],"whyOnRoute":"It slows the day down after the more active morning and gives the final coastal segment a smoother emotional build.","visitBasics":{"hours":"Typically 09:00-18:00; seasonal variation possible","closed":"Open year-round","admission":"Free","walking":"Easy"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Museum and café area","parking":"Available"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"Wider tea-field frames and side-angle café shots usually work better than tight product-only photos.","facilities":"This is one of the most comfortable late-day stops for restrooms, drinks, and seating.","tip":"The stop feels best when treated as a scenic pause with flexible browsing time, not a rushed museum-only visit."}},{"number":6,"time":"15:50","duration":"60 min","name":"Aewol Cafe Street","category":"Café Coast Finish","description":"Aewol closes the day on a lighter note. After mountain air, basalt cliffs, waterfall paths, and tea fields, the route eases into sea views, café decks, and a more leisurely coastal rhythm that works well as a final release.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507525428034-b723cf961d3e?w=800&q=80","highlights":["Ocean-view cafés and an easy late-day walking mood","Handam coastal scenery with a softer, lifestyle-style finish","Flexible time for coffee, photos, and slower pacing","A strong closing contrast to the more active morning"],"timeUsed":["Arrival and short area orientation","Free-paced café or coastal walking time","Meet-up and departure for return transfer"],"whyOnRoute":"Aewol works best as the closing mood of the day, where the pace can open up and the route ends without pressure.","visitBasics":{"hours":"Area open all day; individual café hours vary","closed":"None for the area","admission":"Free","walking":"Easy"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Café facilities vary by venue","parking":"Area parking available"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"Late-day light and side-facing ocean decks usually produce the strongest photos here.","facilities":"Comfort depends on the café selected, so the stop stays flexible rather than fixed to one venue.","tip":"This is the stop where the group benefits most from a looser rhythm instead of a tightly guided schedule."}}],"routeFlowStops":[{"id":"01","name":"Eoseungsaengak","theme":"Hallasan"},{"id":"02","name":"Jusangjeolli","theme":"Coast"},{"id":"03","name":"Lunch","theme":"Reset"},{"id":"04","name":"Cheonjeyeon","theme":"Waterfall"},{"id":"05","name":"O’Sulloc","theme":"Tea"},{"id":"06","name":"Aewol","theme":"Coast"}],"routePhases":[{"label":"Morning","range":"1-2","theme":"Hallasan to coast","bgClass":"bg-sky-50/70","textClass":"text-sky-700","dotClass":"bg-sky-500"},{"label":"Midday","range":"3-4","theme":"Lunch & Waterfall","bgClass":"bg-amber-50/70","textClass":"text-amber-700","dotClass":"bg-amber-500"},{"label":"Finish","range":"5-6","theme":"Tea & Aewol","bgClass":"bg-emerald-50/70","textClass":"text-emerald-700","dotClass":"bg-emerald-500"}],"routeShapeIntro":{"title":"How this day moves","subtitle":"Hallasan to basalt coast, lunch, waterfall, tea fields, then an Aewol coast finish. 09:00 to 17:30."},"whyTourWorks":{"bestFor":["First-time visitors, couples","Adult families","Travelers who want nature, tea fields, and a relaxed finish","Active seniors"],"lessIdeal":["Avoiding stairs or short uphill walks","Stroller-heavy groups","Very young children"],"routeLogicSections":[{"title":"Pacing & structure","icon":"sun","iconBg":"bg-amber-50/80","iconColor":"text-amber-600","items":[{"label":"Hallasan First, While Energy Is Fresh","detail":"Eoseungsaengak works best at the start, when the group can enjoy the short climb before the coastal part of the day begins."},{"label":"Lunch in the Middle, Right on Time","detail":"Lunch resets the day between the more exposed morning and the softer waterfall-and-tea sequence."},{"label":"A Lighter Finish After O’Sulloc","detail":"The route moves through tea fields before ending at Aewol, so the day can release into coffee, sea views, and a more relaxed rhythm."}]},{"title":"Route build","icon":"mountain","iconBg":"bg-sky-50/80","iconColor":"text-sky-600","items":[{"label":"Mountain Before Coast","detail":"The Hallasan start gives the route altitude and texture before the sea opens up at Jusangjeolli."},{"label":"Waterfall Before Tea Fields","detail":"Cheonjeyeon cools the route down first, then O’Sulloc opens it back up with tea-field views and an easier walking rhythm."},{"label":"Café Coast at the End","detail":"Aewol closes the day with a lifestyle-style coastal stop instead of another demanding walk."}]},{"title":"When conditions shift","icon":"wind","iconBg":"bg-slate-50/80","iconColor":"text-slate-600","items":[{"label":"Hallasan Weather Matters","detail":"Eoseungsaengak can be affected by sudden weather changes or trail controls."},{"label":"Wind on the Coast","detail":"Jusangjeolli and Aewol feel more exposed in strong wind than the inland parts of the route."},{"label":"Walking Balance","detail":"The day stays manageable for most travelers, but stairs and short uphill sections still matter at Eoseungsaengak and Cheonjeyeon."}]}]},"practicalAccordionItems":[{"id":"pickup","title":"Pickup & drop-off","preview":"Hotel lobby pickup in Jeju City area","content":["Pickup from your hotel lobby between 08:20-08:50","Return drop-off by approximately 17:50-18:20","Airport pickup available on request","Specific pickup time confirmed the evening before"]},{"id":"walking","title":"Walking & terrain","preview":"Moderate overall, manageable for most","content":["Total walking: approximately 4.5-5.5 km across all stops","Eoseungsaengak: short uphill trail with many stairs","Jusangjeolli: easy coastal viewing paths","Cheonjeyeon: forest paths, stairs, and some wet surfaces","O’Sulloc and Aewol: easy walking with flexible pacing","Comfortable walking shoes strongly recommended"]},{"id":"weather","title":"Weather & closure handling","preview":"Runs in most conditions with adjustments","content":["Light rain: tour proceeds normally","Heavy rain or trail controls: Eoseungsaengak may be shortened or adjusted","Strong wind: Jusangjeolli or Aewol walking time may be reduced","Poor weather later in the day: O’Sulloc can take on a larger role in the route","Site closures: alternative stops may be provided when needed"]},{"id":"wear","title":"What to wear & bring","preview":"Comfortable shoes, layers, light jacket","content":["Walking shoes with good grip","Layers for mountain and coastal temperature changes","Light wind-resistant jacket","Hat and sunscreen","Water bottle"]},{"id":"included","title":"Included / not included","preview":"Guide, vehicle, pickup, admission fees","variant":"included","content":["Professional English-speaking guide","Private or small-group vehicle","Hotel pickup/drop-off (Jeju City)","All admission fees","Bottled water","Lunch (pay directly at restaurant)","Personal shopping","Gratuities"]}],"practicalWeatherStatic":{"today":{"temp":"11°","label":"Today · Clear"},"tomorrow":{"temp":"18°/13°","label":"Tomorrow · Drizzle"}},"seasonalVariations":[{"name":"Spring","icon":"flower","description":"Canola blooms paint the coast gold","tag":"Peak flowers","bgClass":"bg-spring","iconColor":"text-pink-500"},{"name":"Summer","icon":"sun","description":"Extended daylight, vibrant greens","tag":"Longest days","bgClass":"bg-summer","iconColor":"text-sky-500"},{"name":"Autumn","icon":"leaf","description":"Clear skies, crisp visibility","tag":"Best views","bgClass":"bg-autumn","iconColor":"text-amber-600"},{"name":"Winter","icon":"snow","description":"Quieter paths, shorter daylight","tag":"Peaceful mood","bgClass":"bg-winter","iconColor":"text-slate-500"}],"bookingTrustItems":[{"icon":"check-circle","title":"Licensed local","description":"Jeju-licensed guiding","iconBg":"bg-emerald-50/80","iconColor":"text-emerald-600"},{"icon":"route","title":"Route experts","description":"Tuned to southwest flow","iconBg":"bg-sky-50/80","iconColor":"text-sky-600"},{"icon":"users","title":"Small groups","description":"Max 8 guests","iconBg":"bg-amber-50/80","iconColor":"text-amber-600"}],"bookingSupportSteps":[{"timing":"Immediately","title":"Instant Confirmation","detail":"Booking confirmation with itinerary summary"},{"timing":"12 hours before","title":"12-Hour Reminder","detail":"Weather update and any adjustments"},{"timing":"Evening before","title":"Final Pickup Guide","detail":"Exact pickup time and driver contact"},{"timing":"Morning of tour","title":"Day-Of Route Notes","detail":"Morning briefing with conditions"},{"timing":"During tour","title":"Stop-by-Stop Tips","detail":"Real-time guidance at each location"},{"timing":"After tour","title":"Post-Tour Support","detail":"Follow-up and recommendations"}],"staticQuestions":[{"id":"first-time","question":"Is this good for first-time visitors to Jeju?","answer":"Yes. It combines Hallasan scenery, iconic volcanic coastline, a classic waterfall stop, tea-field atmosphere, and a relaxed Aewol finish in one balanced day."},{"id":"walking","question":"Is the walking very difficult?","answer":"Not overall. The most active part is Eoseungsaengak, which is short but stair-heavy, while the rest of the day is moderate for most travelers."},{"id":"rain","question":"Can the tour still run if it rains?","answer":"Yes. The route can be adjusted in wet weather, although Eoseungsaengak and exposed coastal sections may be shortened depending on conditions."},{"id":"parents","question":"Is it okay to join with parents?","answer":"Yes. The route is generally comfortable for adult families, but it is still best for travelers who can manage stairs and short uphill walking."},{"id":"children","question":"Can I join with children?","answer":"Yes. It is better suited to children 8+ who are comfortable with a short hike and a full-day sightseeing pace."},{"id":"order","question":"Can the order change?","answer":"Yes. Mountain weather, wind, traffic, and crowd flow can affect the sequence, especially around Eoseungsaengak and the coastal stops."},{"id":"lunch","question":"Is lunch included?","answer":"That depends on the product setup. The route includes a lunch break in the middle of the day, but meal inclusion depends on your booking fare."},{"id":"why-eoseungsaengak","question":"Why start at Eoseungsaengak?","answer":"It gives the day a real Hallasan opening while the group still has fresh energy, without turning the route into a full mountain hike."},{"id":"why-jusangjeolli","question":"Why visit Jusangjeolli after Hallasan?","answer":"It keeps the volcanic story flowing—from mountain terrain into one of Jeju''s most dramatic basalt coastlines."},{"id":"why-osulloc","question":"Why is O’Sulloc placed before Aewol?","answer":"O’Sulloc works as a calmer transition after the waterfall walk, so the final Aewol stop can feel relaxed instead of rushed."},{"id":"later-structure","question":"Why is the second half structured this way?","answer":"Lunch and Cheonjeyeon soften the route after the more exposed morning, O’Sulloc adds a lighter tea-field pause, and Aewol closes the day without another demanding walking segment."}],"guestReviews":[{"id":1,"author":"Sarah M.","avatar":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1494790108377-be9c29b29330?w=100&q=80","location":"Singapore","date":"March 2024","rating":5,"title":"A really well-balanced southwest Jeju day","text":"The route made real sense—starting on Hallasan gave the day energy, and Jusangjeolli felt even more dramatic after that. We especially liked that O’Sulloc came before Aewol, because the afternoon slowed down in a very natural way.","helpful":24,"verified":true,"tripType":"Couple","photos":["https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506744038136-46273834b3fb?w=400&q=80","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507525428034-b723cf961d3e?w=400&q=80"]},{"id":2,"author":"James K.","avatar":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507003211169-0a1dd7228f2d?w=100&q=80","location":"Hong Kong","date":"March 2024","rating":5,"title":"Great southwest route with a relaxed finish","text":"We''ve done several tours in Korea, and this one stood out for its sequencing. The guide paced Hallasan, the cliffs, and Cheonjeyeon very well, and the O’Sulloc-to-Aewol ending made the whole day feel balanced instead of tiring.","helpful":18,"verified":true,"tripType":"Family","photos":[]},{"id":3,"author":"Yuki T.","avatar":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1438761681033-6461ffad8d80?w=100&q=80","location":"Tokyo","date":"February 2024","rating":4,"title":"Loved Aewol at the end","text":"The overall experience was excellent. Eoseungsaengak was a stronger start than I expected, and O’Sulloc was a really good late-day stop before Aewol. Only reason for 4 stars is I would have liked a little more time at Aewol, but I understand the schedule constraints.","helpful":12,"verified":true,"tripType":"Solo","photos":["https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500530855697-b586d89ba3ee?w=400&q=80"]},{"id":4,"author":"Michael R.","avatar":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500648767791-00dcc994a43e?w=100&q=80","location":"Sydney","date":"February 2024","rating":5,"title":"Much more varied than I expected","text":"Came for the scenery, stayed for the storytelling. The guide connected Hallasan, basalt cliffs, waterfalls, tea fields, and the Aewol coast in a way that made the whole day feel cohesive. The small group size also made transitions much smoother.","helpful":31,"verified":true,"tripType":"Friends","photos":[]}],"reviewsSummary":{"averageRating":4.8,"totalReviews":127,"ratingDistribution":[{"stars":5,"count":98,"percentage":77},{"stars":4,"count":21,"percentage":17},{"stars":3,"count":6,"percentage":5},{"stars":2,"count":1,"percentage":1},{"stars":1,"count":1,"percentage":1}],"highlights":[{"label":"Scenery","count":89},{"label":"Guide","count":76},{"label":"Pacing","count":54},{"label":"Aewol finish","count":41}]},"sticky_booking_bar":{"note":"checkout_tour_id resolves at runtime from Supabase / env; not part of static JSONB.","price":{"amountLabel":"58","currency":"USD","per":"person"}}}'::jsonb
)
